    "title": "Amphibious\" structures", 
    "comments": [
        {
            "date": "2009-10-18 17:16:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Currently, structures can be placed either on the ground or on water. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "A tag for a building would enable all-terrain placement and few tags for artmd.ini would enable special animations to be played if one wanted to have some kind of platform under the structure so it can be placed on water (think Red Alert 3, this was a pretty nice feature).\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "[BUILDING];rulesmd.ini entry\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "AllTerrain=yes\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "[BUILDING];artmd.ini entry\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "WaterAnim.01=\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "WaterAnimDamaged.01=\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "WaterAnimZAdjust.01=\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "WaterAnimYSort.01=\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "WaterAnimIsPowered.01=\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "or simply without those .01, for example WaterAnim and WaterAnimTwo - actually I don't think anyone would need more than one or two animations for naval platform or something similar (platform anim and waves?).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "bug-importer", 
            "email": "bug-importer"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2009-12-21 02:13:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "While this feature would be nice i agree, you can just add a few new buildings in that replicate some of the land buildings that would be useful on water.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I did this with the refinery and made miners amphibious, on many of my maps there are resources on islands surrounded by water.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Besides a naval yard, a radar/airfield, and a refinery, what other buildings would be useful on water?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "bug-importer", 
            "email": "bug-importer"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2009-12-28 02:55:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Power plants are useful, to reduce base clutter. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "But I agree with the person above me. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This has little practicality short of reducing build list clutter.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "genkosygin", 
            "email": "genkosygin"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2009-12-28 06:52:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I love naval bases, and have, in the past, tried to implement them with Naval=yes myself. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "However, especially because I tried stuff like this in the past, I don't think all this work is worth it.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Ultimately, you'll need different buildings anyway. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The threats on (and under) water are entirely different ones, and your buildings need to be adjusted to them. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "For example, I'm rather sure Dolphin vs. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Power Plant balances entirely differently than Grizzly vs. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Power Plant. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "A pillbox on water doesn't make too much sense, either. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Sure, you can give it an image of a machine gun guard tower dropped into water, but...wouldn't a giant, concrete tower have different characteristics than a sandbag'd ground shelter?\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " And wouldn't you think if an army invested the time and money to build a giant sensor phalanx on water (radar buildings), they'd include sensors to detect submarines?\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "In order for this flag to serve a purpose, it should be logical that these buildings are exactly the same both on land and on water. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And it's just not. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It makes more sense to have specialized aquatic versions of each building.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Yes, this does serve minor purposes, so I'm willing to listen to more arguments for it - but to be honest, right now, this looks like way too much work for way too little gain.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "An alternative way to do this would be introducing a WaterVersion=BUILDING flag, which points to a BuildingType to use instead if the user tries to build on water, but, again, this would offer little more than specialized buildings, and would add the confusion of getting an entirely different building than the one you built.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So...any arguments for the introduction of a system like either of these?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "renegade", 
            "email": "renegade"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-07-28 20:34:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I definitely think the \"transforming into a different buildingtype on water\" idea is best. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "While I understand your point about buildings needing to be tailored differently for water or land, Renegade, you are forgetting one very critical detail, and that is that we are talking about mods here. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Yes, that fact alone is stupidly obvious, but what that means is that the modder could have changed a lot with regards to comparisons between land and navy. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Dolphins don't have to be there. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Hell, he could have made a naval grizzly tank for all we know.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It's true that with the stock game, naval and land combat are very different, but there is nothing stopping the modder from changing the balance and making that balance suitable for more involved naval bases.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It's the modder's job to balance their game, not Ares'.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "And of course, not all of your base buildings have to be amphibious; ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "like you said, having a pillbox on the water doesn't make sense, so simply disable building pillboxes on water, and instead have another independent building that shoots torpedoes or other ASW weapons, or whatever the heck you like.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "--\"In order for this flag to serve a purpose, it should be logical that these buildings are exactly the same both on land and on water. And it's just not. It makes more sense to have specialized aquatic versions of each building.\"\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "While what I said above covers most of this, I wanted to add one simple thing and that is this: the land and water variants, while they may differ slightly to adjust to the aforementioned differences between land and water combat, the purposes they serve can and should stay the same. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "A power plant isn't going to provide any more or less power on water or land unless the modder wants to explain why (it gets a personal hydroelectric generator?). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "An airfield will still be an airfield, despite having perhaps a bit more armor.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And even at that, you don't even have to edit the buildings to tailor to naval weapons, you can just edit the naval weapons, particularly their damage values to the buildings in question.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "worminator", 
            "email": "worminator"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-07-28 21:11:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Oh look, it's the typical \"this might, someday, somewhere, perhaps, maybe, potentially, in the undefined future, be useful for an unspecified mod by a hitherto unknown modder\" argumentation.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "How novel and creative.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "What you say is right, of course. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It's entirely possible to craft a mod in which this functionality makes sense and is very useful.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " It's also entirely possible to craft a mod in which units having a sexual desire factor and random dildo rains make perfect sense.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Point is: In 99% of all cases, you can craft a mod around a certain feature. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The truly interesting question is: Is there a demand for it?\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It took seven months for somebody to reply to my question about further arguments. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "There's only one supporter in the ICS system, and that's you. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And even your argumentation is little more than \"it can make sense, if the modder lets it\". ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "No particular demand, no extraordinary usage case, no signs of general community need.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The only sign this feature isn't a complete \"one-hit-wonder\" is BTG's duplicate, and that doesn't provide any argumentation for a specific need, either. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Quoth BTG: \"it opens a lot of possibilities\".\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Basically, everyone agrees that it might, potentially, be useful for some unspecified cases in some unspecified mods, but it doesn't look like the community is actually actively waiting for it.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The community's apparent attitude to this feature can be summed up in two words: \"Why not?\"\r No one's against it, no one argues that it couldn't potentially be useful, no one's here to block it...but no one cares much about whether it's implemented or not, either.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Hell, people care so little, the DFD it's in has only three posts, and in the very first one, Fen outright says he doesn't give a shit:\r Don't care about Fight 1 so I'm not making a vote.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And out of the two support votes it got in that thread, one was explicitly made because...\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " #659 is less stupid\r\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Even the one \"full\" support vote it got went on to point out potential issues with the logic.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This functionality simply isn't in demand.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So while you may be right that, potentially, maybe, sometime in the future, some mod somewhere might be able to do something with it, right now, there's simply no point in implementing this.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It'd be a waste of time.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "renegade", 
            "email": "renegade"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-07-28 21:43:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I support the different version on water, but not strongly. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "More in a \"If it's there I'll use but if it's not, well meh\" way.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "black-temple-gaurdian", 
            "email": "black-temple-gaurdian"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-07-29 04:12:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Even though this issue won its DFD, as outlined there, in my post above, the issue history and kind of confirmed by the preceding comment, there simply doesn't seem to be much interest in this feature.\r", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "After some discussion, we have decided to close this issue due to that. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Should it become apparent in the future that there is substantial interest in this feature, it can be revived, but for now, the request will be closed.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "renegade", 
            "email": "renegade"
        }
    ], 
